[0,\infty)
g(x) = 1
x\in [0,n]
 \lim_{n\to\infty}\int_0^n \left(\frac{n+x}{n+2x}\right)^n dx=\int_0^\infty\left(\lim_{n\to\infty} \left(\frac{n+x}{n+2x}\right)^n \right)\,dx=\int_0^\infty \mathrm{e}^{-x}\,dx=1. 
t=x/n
n \int_0^1 \Bigl(\frac{1+t}{1+2t}\Bigr)^n dt \leq 2n \int_0^1 \Bigl( \frac{1+t}{1+2t}\Bigr)^{n-1} \frac{1}{1+2t} dt = -2 \Bigl( \frac{1+t}{1+2t}\Bigr)^n\Bigr|_0^1 \leq 2. 
